### Description

On Chrome Android with WebGPURenderer, enabling object.receiveShadow = true causes a WGSL validation error (cannot index into expression of type 'f32'). The same scene works when object.receiveShadow is removed or set to false.

```
THREE.WebGPURenderer: Uncaptured WebGPU GPUValidationError: Error while parsing WGSL: :313:33 error: cannot index into expression of type 'f32'
    nodeVar12 = step( nodeVar8.z, textureLoad( nodeUniform16, vec2<u32>( clamp( floor( tsl_coord_clampS_clampT_2d( nodeVar11 ) * vec2<f32>( nodeVar13 ) ), vec2<f32>( 0 ), vec2<f32>( nodeVar13 - vec2<u32>( 1, 1 ) ) ) ), u32( 0 ) ).x );
                                  ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^


 - While calling [Device].CreateShaderModule([ShaderModuleDescriptor ""fragment""]).
```

### Reproduction steps

1. Run code via chrome/inspect on any android device
2. Add/Remove line object.receiveShadow = RECEIVE_SHADOW;
3. Check console errors in browser


