### Suggested fix

Instead of reversing the sorted lists, normalize the sort key when the render item is created, so "smaller z = closer" always holds and the sort functions need no knowledge of reversed depth:

```js
// in projectObject, both renderers
if ( camera.reversedDepth === true ) _vector4.z = - _vector4.z;
```

and drop the `reverse()` blocks from `sort()`. `renderItem.z` is only used for sorting, this keeps the intent of #33700 (front-to-back opaque, back-to-front transparent) and also restores unmodified semantics for custom sort callbacks. PR: incoming.

