Important note: the online jsfiddle is useful as a public reference for the scene setup and code flow, but the Heap Snapshot results captured directly in the online environment are not as stable or trustworthy as the local standalone test. Because of that, my memory observations below are based primarily on the local standalone version, while the jsfiddle is provided mainly as an accessible reproduction reference.

